\pard\pardeftab1134\sl240\ql\qnatural

\f1\fs30 \cf2 Makes:\
\pard\pardeftab1134\sl240\ql\qnatural

\b0 \cf0 22 cakes\
\pard\pardeftab1134\ql\qnatural

\f2\fs34 \cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab1134\sl320\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs46 \cf0 Ingredients\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab1134\li720\fi-720\ri-612\sl400\ql\qnatural

\f1\b0 \cf0 4 cups left over mashed potatoes, or Chive and Onion Mashed Potatoes, recipe follows\
\pard\pardeftab1134\ql\qnatural
\cf0 2 cups panko breadcrumbs, divided
\f2\fs34 \

\f1\fs46 1 large egg, lightly beaten
\f2\fs34 \

\f1\fs46 1/4 cup vegetable oil, plus more, if needed
\f2\fs34 \
\pard\pardeftab1134\sl320\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs46 \cf0 Directions\
\pard\pardeftab1134\sl400\sa140\ql\qnatural

\f1\b0 \cf0 In a large bowl, combine the mashed potatoes, 1 cup panko, and beaten egg. Shape the potato mixture into 3-inch patties. Dredge the patties in the remaining 1 cup panko.\
\pard\pardeftab1134\ql\qnatural

\f2\fs34 \cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab1134\ql\qnatural

\f1\fs46 \cf0 In a large nonstick skillet over medium heat, add the vegetable oil. Add half of the patties and cook until golden brown, 2 to 3 minutes. Repeat the procedure with more oil, if needed, and remaining patties. Serve hot.
\f2\fs34 \
\pard\pardeftab1134\sl320\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs46 \cf0 Chive and Onion Mashed Potatoes:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab1134\li720\fi-720\ri-612\sl400\ql\qnatural

\f1\b0 \cf0 1 1/2 pounds potatoes, peeled and cubed\
\pard\pardeftab1134\ql\qnatural
\cf0 1/2 cup chive and onion cream cheese, softened
\f2\fs34 \

\f1\fs46 1/4 cup butter, softened
\f2\fs34 \
\pard\pardeftab1134\sl400\sa140\ql\qnatural

\f1\fs46 \cf0 Boil the potatoes until done. Pour the potatoes into a medium bowl and add cream cheese and butter. Using a potato masher, mash the potatoes to desired consistency. Serve immediately.\
\pard\pardeftab1134\ql\qnatural

